genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica yucateca
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Originating from the Yucatan Peninsula in Mexico, this genre features traditional instruments such as the jarana and requinto, accompanied by lyrics that depict the region's culture and history. The music is lively and upbeat, often played at social events and celebrations.
